      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FOX DAN (1) has had eight weeks off since he came from the back row for second in the Mildura Cup. Goes very well on the fresh side and the last time he raced here he won the Victoria Derby. Should get every chance from the ace draw. OLIVER DAN (3) had put together a string of top-four finishes before he relished a better draw and returned to the winners' list here last time. Strikes at 50 per cent at this longer distance and gets a similar barrier so could strike again. MY ULTIMATE BARNEY (4) continues to race well having placed in both outings since a Geelong win. He has recorded three wins and two placings in six tries over this longer distance here so this suits. DANGEROUS (8) raced wide but proved too good at Wagga last start. Draws to track FOX DAN early and could be dangerous. Last season's Vicbred winner ITS CONFIDENTIAL (6) rises in grade off the fresh win in Sydney but has upside.",
